<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-07T19:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-07T19:29:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/707.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-07T19:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 7, 1912—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Ferrara, left today on
                            unannounced trip to Washington. I am reliably informed he is special
                            representative of President Gómez to ask further aid in protecting
                            property, but more particularly to plead for time to crush rebellion.
                            This information is from private sources.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>